Package ai.test.sdk

Class TestAiDriver<T>

java.lang.Object
ai.test.sdk.TestAiDriver<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The element type to return, must be a subclass of MobileElement.
public class TestAiDriver<T> extends Object
A convenient wrapper around AppiumDriver which calls out to Test.ai to improve the accuracy of identified elements.
Author:
Alexander Wu (alec@test.ai)

  • Constructor Details

    • TestAiDriver

      public TestAiDriver(AppiumDriver<MobileElement> driver, String apiKey, String serverURL, String testCaseName, boolean train) throws IOException
      Constructor, creates a new TestAiDriver.
      Parameters:
      driver - The AppiumDriver to wrap
      apiKey - Your API key, acquired from sdk.test.ai.
      serverURL - The server URL. Set null to use the default of sdk.test.ai.
      testCaseName - The test case name to use for interactive mode. Setting this to something other than null enables interactive mode.
      train - Set `true` to enable training for each encountered element.
      Throws:
      IOException - If there was an initialization error.
